  "title": "Lollipop Chainsaw anime announced",
  "text": "Lollipop Chainsaw anime announced\nLollipop Chainsaw Man?\nLollipop Chainsaw has had a resurgence in popularity since the game’s remaster, Lollipop Chainsaw RePOP, was released last year. Now, Dragami Games and Nada Holdings are partnering to produce a whole host of new Lollipop Chainsaw content, and we’ve just learned about their initial plans.\nIt was announced today that we’re getting an official Lollipop Chainsaw anime adaptation. As of now, there’s no word about what studio will be behind the series, when it’s planned to air, or really any details at all. We’ll have to hold on until they’re ready to reveal exactly what this anime will entail.\nIn addition, a brand new Lollipop Chainsaw video game was announced. Details about this were just as scarce, and no platforms have been confirmed, but we’ll keep an eye on things in case it ends up coming to Switch 2.\nGematsu]",
